The paper presents a novel approach to job scheduling in cluster systems using deep reinforcement learning. This involves optimizing for both energy consumption and performance, which are critical concerns in designing computing devices. Given the focus on machine learning and optimization, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.PF (Performance).
